\[
C = \frac{(c-d)(c-a)}{c+d+a}, D = \frac{(d-a)(d-b)}{d+a+b} \text{. }
\]

Then \( 2A = A' + A'' \), where,
\[
A' = \frac{(a-c)^2}{a+b+c}, A'' = \frac{(a-c)(a-2b+c)}{a+b+c} \text{. }
\]

Similarly, we have
\[
2B = B' + B'', 2C = C' + C'', 2D = D' + D'' \text{. }
\]

Let \( s = a + b + c + d \). Then the denominators of \( A, B, C, D \) are \( s-d, s-a, s-b, s-c \), respectively.
By the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality, we get
\[
\begin{array}{l}
\left(\frac{|a-c|}{\sqrt{s-d}} \cdot \sqrt{s-d} + \frac{|b-d|}{\sqrt{s-a}} \cdot \sqrt{s-a} + \right. \\
\left. \frac{|c-a|}{\sqrt{s-b}} \cdot \sqrt{s-b} + \frac{|d-b|}{\sqrt{s-c}} \cdot \sqrt{s-c}\right)^2 \\
\leqslant \left[\frac{(a-c)^2}{s-d} + \frac{(b-d)^2}{s-a} + \frac{(c-a)^2}{s-b} + \right. \\
\left. \frac{(d-b)^2}{s-c}\right](4s - s) \\
= 3s \left(A' + B' + C' + D'\right) \text{. }
\end{array}
\]

Thus, \( A' + B' + C' + D' \)
\[
\begin{array}{l}
\geqslant \frac{(2|a-c| + 2|b-d|)^2}{3s} \\
\geqslant \frac{16|a-c| \cdot |b-d|}{3s} \text{. }
\end{array}
\]

\( A'' + C'' \)
\[
\begin{array}{l}
= \frac{(a-c)(a+c-2b)}{s-d} + \frac{(c-a)(c+a-2d)}{s-b} \\
= \frac{(a-c)(a+c-2b)(s-b) + (c-a)(c+a-2d)(s-d)}{(s-d)(s-b)} \\
= \frac{(a-c)[-2b(s-b) - b(a+c) + 2d(s-d) + d(a+c)]}{s(a+c) + bd} \\
= \frac{3(a-c)(d-b)(a+c)}{M} \text{, }
\end{array}
\]

where \( M = s(a+c) + bd \).
Similarly, \( B'' + D'' = \frac{3(b-d)(a-c)(b+d)}{N} \),

where \( N = s(b+d) + ca \).
Thus, \( A'' + B'' + C'' + D'' \)
\[
\begin{array}{l}
= 3(a-c)(b-d)\left(\frac{b+d}{N} - \frac{a+c}{M}\right) \\
= \frac{3(a-c)(b-d)W}{MN} \text{, }
\end{array}
\]

where \( W = (b+d)M - (a+c)N \)
\[
\begin{array}{l}
= (b+d)bd - (a+c)ac \text{. } \\
\text{Also, } MN = s^2(a+c)(b+d) + s(a+c)ac + \\
\quad s(b+d)bd + abcd \\
> s[(a+c)ac + (b+d)bd] \geqslant |W|s \text{, (3) }
\end{array}
\]

Then, by equations (2) and (3), we get
\[
\left|A'' + B'' + C'' + D''\right| \leqslant \frac{3|a-c| \cdot |b-d|}{s} \text{. }
\]

Combining with equation (1), we get
\[
\begin{array}{l}
2(A + B + C + D) \\
= \left(A' + B' + C' + D'\right) + \left(A'' + B'' + C'' + D''\right) \\
\geqslant \frac{16|a-c| \cdot |b-d|}{3s} - \frac{3|a-c| \cdot |b-d|}{s} \\
= \frac{7|a-c| \cdot |b-d|}{3(a + b + c + d)} \geqslant 0 \text{. }
\end{array}
\]

Therefore, the original inequality holds, and the equality holds when \( a = c, b = d \).

